    <note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Q. I. Hilarianus Bishop and theologian in Africa, 4th cent. AD, Lived in the second half of the 4th cent. AD. This bishop, who (presumably) resided in North Africa, was the author of two texts of AD 397: De ratione Paschae et mensis (‘On the calculation of Eastertide’) and De cursu temporum, a world history...." Fröhlich, Roland (Tübingen). “Iulius”, in: Brill’s New Pauly, Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Consulted online on 08 November 2016</note>
